# JWT Authentication Implementation Plan

## Context

This Express API currently has no authentication. All POST/PUT/DELETE routes are open, `userId` is accepted from the request body (defaulting to `1`), and there is no ownership enforcement. The goal is to add a full JWT auth system so that:
- Users can register and log in to receive a JWT token
- POST/PUT/DELETE on `/posts` and `/comments` require a valid Bearer token
- `userId` on new resources comes from the token, not the request body
- Only the resource owner can update or delete their own posts/comments (403 otherwise)
- All GET routes remain public
- All existing tests continue to pass; new `tests/auth.test.ts` tests pass

JWT secret: `"super-secret-key"`. No new npm packages needed — `jsonwebtoken@^9.0.0` and `@types/jsonwebtoken` are already installed.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Action |
|---|---|
| `src/types.ts` | Modify — add Express `Request` type augmentation |
| `src/middleware/auth.ts` | **Create** — JWT verification middleware |
| `src/routes/auth.ts` | **Create** — register + login endpoints |
| `src/routes/posts.ts` | Modify — protect POST/PUT/DELETE, enforce ownership |
| `src/routes/comments.ts` | Modify — protect POST/PUT/DELETE, enforce ownership |
